  <title translate="true">Basic Concept</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Basic Concept</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="clip0064.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold;" translate="true">KRT software using Test Center managing all the test parameters and control the testing procedure, All parameters in test center stored in a test template(.KRT format file). </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Test results can export as RTF or XML format, RTF format for print purpose, like a .DOC file, XML format file can import to test center for review the testing scene.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading HowTo_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading HowTo_atoc_" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold;" translate="true">3 preparatory steps are required in order to ensure a successful test:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">The scope of preparatory steps depends on the complexity of the desired test.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:0px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="3" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:5%;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">1.</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:0px;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Defining the hardware configurations of the test kit to match the specific modules.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:5%;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">2.</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:0px;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Entering relay settings in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Test_Object" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Test Object</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:5%;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">3.</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">Setting the binary inputs trigger conditions to which the relay contacts connected, to measure the trip time correctly</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:0px;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt;" translate="true">If these preparatory steps are completed, then go to test modules for particular test.</text></para>
